This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically traffic sign recognition, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also discusses the optimization of network parameters and computations, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of embedded devices is also mentioned, which could suggest the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper discusses the real-world applications of traffic sign recognition, which could suggest the cs.RO (Robotics) category.
